OL,3,CMum bids to buy church for disabled
OL,4,Cson due to lack of suitable homes
OL,6,FHer son, Hero, was diagnosed with
OL,7,FDuchenne muscular dystrophy (DMD) as a
OL,8,Ftoddler. The condition has no cure and
OL,9,Fmeans muscles become weaker until
OL,10,Fpatients need help to breathe. People
OL,11,Fwith DMD usually live into their teens.
OL,13,FRachel, 39, a former nurse, said: "In
OL,14,Four hope to adapt our home we have
OL,15,Ffound that the grant from local
OL,16,Fcouncils to support that adaptation
OL,17,Fhasn't changed in over 16 years ` it's
OL,18,F#30,000.
OL,20,F"To get our home right will cost over
OL,21,F#50,000... We just can't afford it.
