OL,6,FCllr Moses Crook said: "As a local
OL,7,Fauthority, we receive a portion of the
OL,8,FDepartment for Levelling Up, Housing
OL,9,Fand Communities' Disabled Facilities
OL,10,FGrant, aimed at supporting residents
OL,11,Fwith disabilities in adapting their
OL,12,Fhomes for independent living.
OL,14,F"We recognise the frustrations that
OL,15,Fcome with these limitations. Although
OL,16,Fthe council is guided by the
OL,17,Fgovernment-set maximum grant,
OL,18,Fdependent on individual circumstances,
OL,19,Fthere are discretionary funding
OL,20,Foptions that we are committed to
OL,21,Fhelping residents explore.
